 Dostoevsky’s signature style. It investigates the changes that Dostoevsky made while working on Balzac’s text and analyzes the complex transplantation of Balzac’s imagery, motifs, and character portraiture from Eugénie Grandet into Dostoevsky’s own writing later on.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Comparative Literature.2bisacsh  aBalzac.  aDostoevsky.  aEugénie Grandet, nineteenth-century novel.  aFrench literature.  aRussian literature.  acomparative literature.  acultural studies.  aliterary translation.  atranslation studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076741408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644697801zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644697801423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644697801/original  a978-3-11-076741-4  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK